parameters:
This is the enchanted forest--a tranquil place filled with
nature.
Such a vast forest... It's almost like a sea of trees.

It's been a while since we've been here. Nothing seems to
have changed since then.
Momiji-san, have you been to this forest before?

Yes. I met my master here when I was still under the control
of the demon's power. If not for that encounter, I might
have lost my humanity long ago. I might never have met you,
Karin-chan and Yugiri-san...

This place feels so sacred, as if just breathing in the air
purifies your body.

My master said the same. Thanks to the purifying effect of
this forest, the spirits and animals are calm, making it
less dangerous and harmful than other forests.

The battle demon named Senbi that we saw at the coastal
cave, right?

Grrr--I'm honored you remember my name. Gyoun predicted that
you would come here, and it seems he was right. Your goal is
the sword known as the demon-slaying divine weapon, isn't
it?

You know about the Divine Threefold Sword? Did you come here
to prevent us from obtaining it?

Hmph, such a legendary sword is merely bait. It seems my
archenemy Masaki has not come here. What a letdown.

I will slash your body again and feast on your innards! It
would be fitting for you to die miserably, pierced by my
claws!

--!? (So fast! I could barely follow with my eyes...! He's
the quickest opponent we've faced so far!)
I'm... okay, Momiji-san... it's just a scratch...

Hmph! Slow, sluggish--you're not even worth my effort. Did
you expect too much?

Momiji, how dare you betray us, the Eight Grudge Battle
Demons? Kotaro- was lamenting. What a disgraceful
daughter...

...I decide how I live my life. You're an outsider to our
parent-child relationship; it's not your place to comment so
casually.

Hmph--you've completely lost your demonic edge and become so
human-like. Is it because of your master Masaki? I was
surprised that after being slashed up so badly half a year
ago, she didn't die and is still alive.
...! Could it be that Senbi is--?

Yes. He's the one who attacked our master half a year ago
and reduced her to just a fox form. He's a monstrous being
who fell into the path of demons after being defeated by our
master over a hundred years ago.

I can't stand that a mere fox thinks it's superior to a
wolf. Killing Masaki and becoming the king of spirits is my
lifelong ambition--I have no interest in weak humans like
you. My subordinates, ferocious beasts, will take care of
you.

Wait right there, Senbi! Are you planning to tuck your tail
and run after starting a fight!?

Gwahahahahaha! For someone who has taken my claw strikes
twice and still barks, you're quite spirited! I'll be
waiting at the innermost shrine of the enchanted forest. If
you wish to die, come anytime!

--Senbi leapt away with a great jump and disappeared into
the depths of the forest!

Hmm, what to do... I talked big, but that wolf demon is
incredibly fast and strong...

Shall we return to Edo for now? It might be wise to seek
assistance from Lady Masaki.

No, we can handle a battle demon like him on our own. Let's
continue deeper into the forest. If we're careless with
time, Senbi might hide the legendary sword somewhere...

Yes, you're right, Momiji-san. Since we came to the
enchanted forest by ourselves to search for the Jintsumei
Sword, let's challenge Senbi to a duel with just the three
of us here.

Indeed. Understood. Let's proceed carefully to the inner
areas--
